column1: # This csv file list the private loggers we have in the system. There must be at least
# The first column is the name of the logger (must be unique of course). This is identical
# to the value passed to the Logger.getLogger call.
# The second argument specifies the fully qualified class name of the logger factory
# to create the logger. This should be blank for almost most of our loggers. In the special
# situation where the logger is a subclass of ariba.util.log.Logger
# the logger factory. The only example we currently have is the 'Audit Logger'
# created by ariba.base.log.AuditLoggerFactory. Since subclasses of ariba.util.log.Logger is
# unusual (and is definitely not for the faint hearted)
column2: all such loggers are private loggers.
